# Cronicle job for Lodore Permit Bot — run every 5 minutes
#
# In Cronicle, create a job with:
#
#   Working Directory:  /opt/River_Permit_Tracker
#   Command:            ./.venv/bin/python3 lodore_permit_bot-2.py
#   Schedule:           Every 5 min (or cron: */5 * * * *)
#   Run as:             root (or user that owns the repo and .env)
#
# Logs: Cronicle shows stdout/stderr per run; the bot also writes to
#       lodore_bot.log in the working directory.
#
# Optional second job to pull code updates daily:
#   Working Directory:  /opt/River_Permit_Tracker
#   Command:            ./scripts/update.sh
#   Schedule:           Daily at 3:00 AM (or similar)
